item.description:
Subclasses: Path, Circle, Text, Image
The Mark class represents a primitive building block of a visualization. There are different types of marks, implemented as the child classes of Mark: Path, Circle, Text, and Image.
Properties property explanation type default value bounds the bounding rectangle of the mark Rectangle dataScope the data scope of the mark DataScope undefined fillColor the fill color of the mark Color undefined id the unique id of the mark String opacity the opacity of the mark (between 0 and 1) Number 1 strokeColor the stroke color of the mark Color undefined strokeDash the dashes and gaps for the mark stroke String undefined strokeWidth the stroke width of the mark in pixels Number undefined type the type of the mark String visibility whether the mark is visible (&ldquo;visible&rdquo; or &ldquo;hidden&rdquo;) String &ldquo;visible&rdquo;
